.cs 2 on
.cs 3 on
.item 'XPAUSE Statement' 'Added on 08/13/87 by AHJ'
.boxon
XPAUSE [MSG='message']
.boxoff

.* DESCRIPTION
(** Extended EXECs only **)
The XPAUSE statement stops execution of an Extended EXEC file at the XPAUSE
statement, returning control to the Command prompt but leaving you at the
current level of the current procedure.  This is useful for debugging.  You
can continue the execution of the EXEC with the XGO command.

.* SELECT 'XPAUSE Statement Options'
.us Option Descriptions

.* OPTION MSG
.optix MSG
MSG='message'\\\an optional message that is displayed at the terminal before
                the Command prompt is reissued.
.cs 2 off
.cs 3 off
